    <div class="lesson-content-title">Exponentials and Natural Logs</div>
    <div class="lesson-content-body">
        <div class="lesson-content-memo">e= 2.718281828459045235360287471352662497757247093699959574966...</div>
        
        As a mathematical constant, e = 2.71828...
        <br/>ln(x) = log<sub>e</sub>(x) where x > 0.
        
        <br/>
        <br/><strong>Useful Identities:</strong>
        <ul style="list-style-type:none">
            <li>ln(e<sup>x</sup>)= x</li> 
            <li>ln(e)= 1</li> 
            <li>e<sup>ln(x)</sup>= x</li>
        </ul>

        <strong>Useful Properties:</strong>
        <ol>
            <li>ln(1) = 0<br/><br/></li> 
            
            <li>ln(x*y) = ln(x) + ln(y)
                <br>     &nbsp; example: &nbsp; ln(45) = ln(5*9) = ln(5) + ln(9)<br/><br/></li>
            
            <li>ln(x/y) = ln(x) - ln(y)
            <br>    &nbsp; example: &nbsp; ln(5) = ln(45/9) = ln(45) - ln(9)<br/><br/></li>
            
            <li>ln(x<sup>y</sup>) = y*ln(x)</li>
        </ol>

        <br>
        <strong>Worked Example: Solve for x when:
        <font color=blue>A</font> = e<sup>x</sup></strong>
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; <font color=blue>A</font> = e<sup>x</sup>
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; ln(A) = ln(e<sup>x</sup>)
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; ln(A) = x*ln(e)
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; ln(A) = x*1
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; x = ln(A)

        <br/><br/>
        <strong>Worked Example: Solve for x when:
          <font color=blue>A</font> = ln(5x)</strong>
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; <font color=blue>A</font> = ln(5x)
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; e<sup>A</sup> = e<sup>ln(5x)</sup>
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; e<sup>A</sup> = 5x
        <br>&nbsp; &nbsp; x = e<sup>A</sup>/5

